author: Society Today
text: Nobody believes that Civil Servants Commission was or is faire. To find out that, if you visit any government offices, across the country, 97% officers represent only one caste people, whereas that caste ethnic people are only 12% of total population. Visiting the government offices, there is hardly any other ethic people I.e. Newar, Gurung, Magar, forget about the low caste truly marginalised people in the civil service. To consume the majority of the national budget, only one group of ethnic people having all the great opporutinity, what type of Democracy is it? Or there should be no term as Caste in Nepal or else all should have the faire opportunity. At the moment, it is not faire & sensible for Nepal in the 21st C. Civil Service Commission is hijacked by one caste group. So abolish the current commission to make a new one where all people are represented.
